
// Connects to a MySQL database and executes an SQL statement loaded from a file. The [mysql.connect] slot establishes a connection to the database, while the [mysql.execute] slot executes the SQL statement, which is dynamically loaded using [io.file.load]. This setup allows for executing SQL commands stored in external files, facilitating modular and maintainable database operations.
mysql.connect
   mysql.execute:x:@io.file.load
